<br>
::The appearance of Hecate suprised him somewhat, as Hecate was a goddess that he rarely saw. He smiled cordially to her, but did not say anything as she didn't walk up, or even acknowledge his presense::<br>
<br>
::Hephaestus hammered away on the chain, his hands were now had a red glow, the same kind of glow that was in heated metal. The chain itself started taking on the same red glow that was within his hands, one could easily surmise that this was a transfer of magic::<br>
<br>
::Within what seemed no time, Hephaestus was linking the chain back together link by link, as he imbued each link with magic, as well as the lock. The glow still strong upon the chain. His hands were touching the hot chain, and not getting burned. He was of course also God of Fire.::<br>
<br>
::He then hoisted the enormous chain over his shoulder and dragged it back to the door. He placed the chain and the lock back upon the door. It still glowed a bright red. He then raised his hand. He then muttered something, and the magic stabilized upon the chain::<br>
<br>
::He then clapped his hands together:: &quot;Not the prettiest piece of work I've done, but just as strong, if not moreso. If Prometheus could not break his chains, the combined might of the Titans will NEVER break this one. Plus the magic wards I have placed upon them. Nothing will EVER get in, and nothing will EVER get out.&quot;<br>
<br>
::He then waved his hands over the pit of fire, and it began cooling. He then picked up his tools, his hammer and his anvil, though they still be hot, with no problem::<br>
<br>
&quot;Now if you'll be so kind Uncle Hades. My payment and then a return trip to Aetna.&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=persephoneqofu>PersephoneQofU</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Bronze Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 200<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(5/5/03 5:06 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=302.topic&index=54>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.aishwarya-rai.com/tradi/tash16.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Better</span><hr size=1> ::The royal physician walks up to Hades and Hephaestus and bows kneels politely. Upon seeing the new chains, his gives a sigh of great relief::<br>
